-- Nomura’s Global Markets Head Jotwani Said to Plan Stepping Down
-- B y   T a k a h i k o   H y u g a
-- 2012-01-10T16:50:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/nomura-s-global-markets-head-jotwani-said-to-plan-stepping-down.html
Tarun Jotwani, head of the global
markets unit at  Nomura Holdings Inc. (8604) , has agreed to step down
and the Japanese brokerage will split up the division, according
to a person with knowledge of the matter.  Nomura’s fixed-income and equities businesses will be
managed as separate units as part of the restructuring, the
person said, declining to be identified as the matter is
confidential. Jotwani, who is based in  London , will also quit
the firm, the person said.  Joey Wu, a spokeswoman for Nomura in Tokyo, declined to
comment. Jotwani and his assistant weren’t immediately available
at Nomura’s office in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Takahiko Hyuga in Tokyo at 
